<h1>The<br>
Toast Point<br>
Page!</h1>
<hr>
</center>
Welcome to <a href=bio.html>Eric Peterson</a>'s <em>Toast Point
Page</em>, celebrating all that is scintillating and tweaks one in
interesting places!   Why Toast Point? <B><I>Toast Point</I></B> is
a term of endearment
from my <A HREF = "wumpus.html">Wumpus</A>!
<p>
<center>
<a href=#news>News</a> * 
<a href=#contests>Contests</a> * 
<a href= #links>Links</a> * 
<a href=#other>Other</a>
</center>
<hr>
<center><h2><a name="news">News</a></h2></center>
<b>December</b> -<br>
Wumpus and Toast Point are frantically preparing for the 
holidays, as they are hosting multitudinous dinner parties.  Toast 
Point had two business trips in two weeks (Philadelphia, where he 
visited old haunts and old friends, and Chicago, which was fun) and is now 
preparing to play Pish-Tush in a concert Mikado at CAMI Hall, 57th St., across 
from Carnegie Hall on Dec. 17th, 8:00 p.m. (it's free! Come see him!),
<p>
<h4>Within the last months...</h4>
Toast Point has
delightedly discovered <a
href=http://www.fortunecity.com/skyscraper/centre/106/index.html>MAME</a>, which lets him
play original arcade games and is reliving his college days by incessantly playing Crystal
Castles.<p>
The <a href=midi/midi.html>MIDI Files</a> page, with aural examples of the original musical
compositions of Toast Point!<p>
Marianne and <a href=http://keck.ucsf.edu/~holder>Gaylord</a> had a baby boy on June 30th!
<p> 
The San Francisco Bay Area <a href=travel/bayarea.html>travelogue</a> now has pictures and
links!
<p>
My <a href=bio.html>bio</a> has been updated with a picture of my parents!
<p>

The <a href=fiction/fiction.html>Bad Fiction Contest</a> now has a <a
href=fiction/fictfrm2.html>new entry option</a>.
